wex inc wex company profile  reuterscom x edition united states africa américa latina عربي argentina brasil canada  deutschland españa france india italia  méxico россия united kingdom united states profile wex inc wex related topics stocksstock screenerindustrialsbusiness support services overview news key developments people charts financials analysts research pulse wex on new york consolidated usd  aug  change  chg   prev close  open  days high  days low  volume  avg vol  wk high  wk low  full description wex inc incorporated on june   is a provider of corporate payment solutions the company operates through three segments fleet solutions travel and corporate solutions and health and employee benefit solutions the fleet solutions segment provides customers with fleet vehicle payment processing services designed for the needs of commercial and government fleets the fleet solutions segment also provides information management services to these fleet customers the travel and corporate solutions segment focuses on the complex payment environment of businesstobusiness payments providing customers with payment processing solutions for their corporate payment and transaction monitoring needs the health and employee benefit solutions segment provides healthcare payment products and software as a service saas consumer directed platforms as well as payroll related benefits to customers in brazil the united states operations include the company and its subsidiaries wex bank wex fleetone electronic funds source llc efs and wex health its international operations include its subsidiaries wex fuel cards australia wex prepaid cards australia wex new zealand wex europe limited unik sa referred to as wex brazil and wex europe services limited and its subsidiariesfleet solutionsthe companys fleet solutions segment provides fleet vehicle payment processing services with over  million vehicles using its fleet payment solutions to purchase fuel and maintenance services its fleet products are based upon technology with closedloop networks in the united states australia and europe and site acceptance domestically and abroad it delivers security through individualized driver identification and realtime transaction updates purchase controls and reporting tools it collects a range of information at the point of sale including the amount of the expenditure the identity of the driver and vehicle the odometer reading the identity of the fuel or vehicle maintenance provider and the items purchased it uses this information to provide customers with analytical tools to allow them manage their vehicle fleets and control costs it provides customized offerings to its customers for accepting merchants processing payments and providing information management products and services to fleets its closedloop networks allow it to provide its customers with detailed fleetspecific information and customized controls that are not available on openloop networks such as limiting purchases to fuel only and restricting the time of day and day of the week when fuel is purchasedthe company offers customer service account activation and account retention services to fleets and fleet management companies and the fuel and vehicle maintenance providers on its network its services include promoting the adoption and use of its products and programs and account retention programs on behalf of its customers and partners it handles authorization and billing questions account changes and other issues for fleets through its customer contact centers fleet customers also have selfservice options available to them through its websites it assigns designated account managers to businesses and government agencies with fleets it offers account approval credit management and fraud detection programs its representatives work with fuel and vehicle maintenance providers to enroll these providers in its network test all network and terminal software and hardware and to provide training on the sale transaction authorization and settlement processestravel and corporate solutionsthe companys travel and corporate solutions segment consists of virtual and prepaid products it allows businesses to centralize purchasing simplify complex supply chain processes and eliminate the paper check writing associated with traditional purchase order programs its product suite includes virtual credit debit and prepaid products its virtual card is used for transactions where no card is presented including transactions conducted over the telephone by mail by fax or on the internet its virtual card also can be used for transactions that require preauthorization such as hotel reservations under its virtual card programs each transaction is assigned an account number with a customized credit limit and expiration date the account number limits purchase amounts and tracks and settles and reconciles purchases the virtual card products offer both credit and debit options its prepaid and gift card products are offered through wex prepaid card australia and wex europe limited to companies throughout australia and europe these products provide secure payment and financial management solutions with single card options access to open or closed loop redemption load limits and variable expirationshealth and employee benefit solutionsthe companys health and employee benefit solutions segment product suite includes its pay and plan payment solution products and its exchangepoint cloud and direct saas platforms with its healthcare payment products it provides payments in the healthcare market it partners with health plans thirdparty administrators financial institutions payroll companies and software providers to provide a saas product to support employers healthcare benefits programs and to administer flexible spending health saving and reimbursement accounts and other healthcare related employee and dependent benefits its paycard products are offered through its subsidiary wex brazil its health and employee benefit solutions products and services to consumers through an extensive partner network which includes health plans third party administrators financial institutions payroll providers and software providers its employee benefit products are marketed to consumers through employers in brazil » full overview of wex company address wex inc  darling avesouth portland   me    p f  company web links home page officers  directors name compensation michael dubyak  melissa smith  rowland moriarty  roberto simon  hilary rapkin  » more officers  directors wex inc news briefwex q adjusted nongaap earnings per share  jul   briefwex inc announces plans for potential debt repricing jun   briefwex q gaap earnings per share  apr   ondeck capital shares plunge on downbeat outlook feb   update ondeck capital shares plunge on downbeat outlook feb   » more wex news related topics stocksstock screenerindustrialsbusiness support services products by wex inc  fleet management marketplacewex incproductsproducts by wex inc rating    reviewswrite a review  otr pro cardthe otr pro card is a simple costeffective solution designed specifically for the trucking industry to help gain operational efficiencies and save money the program offers prenegotiated fuel discounts no fuel transaction fees access to realtime transaction data and comprehensive read morerapid paycardrapid paycard was established in  and is focused on employer payroll card programs rapid paycards mission is to help clients achieve a legally compliant  electronic payroll that benefits the employer financially improves the lives of their employees and creates a more sustainable read moreuniversal fleet cardwright express is a leading global provider of payment processing and information management services wright express captures and combines transaction information from its proprietary network with specialized analytical tools and purchasing control capabilities in a suite of solutions that read morewright express